OL,3,COwner of Reading FC 'open to the sale'
OL,4,Cof club's Bearwood Park training ground
OL,6,FThe owner of Reading Football Club,
OL,7,FDai Yongge, said he is "open to the
OL,8,Fsale" of the club's training ground,
OL,9,Fin order to raise short-term funds.
OL,11,Fdue to financial issues, after a
OL,12,Fdecision by an EFL Disciplinary
OL,13,FCommission last month.
OL,15,FIn a statement, the club said: "Mr
OL,16,FDai, is currently evaluating every
OL,17,Foption at present to secure sufficient
OL,18,Ffunding until new ownership is
OL,19,Fconfirmed. In doing so, he is open to
OL,20,Fthe sale of Bearwood Park, should an
OL,21,Fappropriate offer be received.
